[2] Diarrhea - Nepal (Saptari District)
Date: Wed 4 Jun 2014
Source: My Republica [edited]
http://www.myrepublica.com/portal/index.php?action=news_details&news_id=76324


Diarrhea outbreak has gripped a Dalit settlement at Terhauta VDC-3 in [Saptari] district since last few days. As many as 60 people in the settlement are suffering from diarrhea. About a dozen of them are undergoing treatment at the Sagarmatha Zonal Hospital, while others in the village itself under the supervision of doctors, Senior Public Health Officer Bijaya Kumar Jha said.

So far, no one has died of the disease in the village. A team of doctors with necessary medicines has been providing treatment, he added.

Children and the elderly people are affected the most by the disease. The settlement is some 15 kilometers [9 mi] from the district headquarters Rajbiraj.

